events.name: .ajaxComplete()
events.description: Register a handler to be called when Ajax requests complete. This is an AjaxEvent.

events.name: .ajaxError()
events.description: Register a handler to be called when Ajax requests complete with an error. This is an Ajax Event.

events.name: .ajaxSend()
events.description: Attach a function to be executed before an Ajax request is sent. This is an Ajax Event.

events.name: .ajaxStart()
events.description: Register a handler to be called when the first Ajax request begins. This is an Ajax Event.

events.name: .ajaxStop()
events.description: Register a handler to be called when all Ajax requests have completed. This is an Ajax Event.

events.name: .ajaxSuccess()
events.description: Attach a function to be executed whenever an Ajax request completes successfully. This is an Ajax Event.

events.name: .blur()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “blur” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .change()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “change” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .click()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “click” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .contextmenu()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “contextmenu” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .dblclick()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “dblclick” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .focus()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “focus” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .focusin()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “focusin” event.

events.name: .focusout()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “focusout” JavaScript event.

events.name: .hover()
events.description: Bind one or two handlers to the matched elements, to be executed when the mouse pointer enters and leaves the elements.

events.name: .keydown()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “keydown” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .keypress()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “keypress” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .keyup()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “keyup” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .mousedown()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “mousedown” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .mouseenter()
events.description: Bind an event handler to be fired when the mouse enters an element, or trigger that handler on an element.

events.name: .mouseleave()
events.description: Bind an event handler to be fired when the mouse leaves an element, or trigger that handler on an element.

events.name: .mousemove()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “mousemove” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .mouseout()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “mouseout” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .mouseover()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “mouseover” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .mouseup()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “mouseup” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .off()
events.description: Remove an event handler.

events.name: .on()
events.description: Attach an event handler function for one or more events to the selected elements.

events.name: .one()
events.description: Attach a handler to an event for the elements. The handler is executed at most once per element per event type.

events.name: .ready()
events.description: Specify a function to execute when the DOM is fully loaded.

events.name: .resize()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “resize” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .scroll()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “scroll” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .select()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “select” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .submit()
events.description: Bind an event handler to the “submit” JavaScript event, or trigger that event on an element.

events.name: .trigger()
events.description: Execute all handlers and behaviors attached to the matched elements for the given event type.

events.name: .triggerHandler()
events.description: Execute all handlers attached to an element for an event.
